comment: Gasol (CHI) makes body to body contact with Gobert (UTA) that affects his RSBQ at the start of the drive.
Hood (UTA) grabs and holds Butler (CHI) affecting his FOM and ability to catch the entry pass.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Gasol (CHI) prior to going OOB was confirmed.
Moore (CHI) makes contact with Hood's (UTA) body that affects his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Favors (UTA) and Gasol (CHI) briefly engage and separate away from the ball.
Hayward (UTA) and Gasol (CHI) briefly engage and separate away from the ball.
Gasol (CHI) makes a legal spin move to the basket with Hayward (UTA) defending him.
Gobert (UTA) does not intentionally kick the ball on the play.
Gobert (UTA) does not move his pivot foot (left foot) after ending his dribble.
Gibson (CHI) makes contact with Gobert's (UTA) arm that affects his layup attempt.
Butler (CHI) makes contact with Hayward's (UTA) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
Gasol (CHI) obtains a legal guarding position and jumps vertically to contest Hayward's (UTA) driving layup attempt.

After communicating with the Replay Center, there was conclusive video evidence that showed that Butler (CHI) touched the ball last prior to it going OOB. The ruling on the court was overturned and Utah was awarded possession.
Moore (CHI) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Hayward (UTA) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Gibson (CHI) sets the screen on Hood (UTA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Hood (UTA) reaches in and makes contact with Gibson (CHI) causing him to lose possession of the ball.
Gibson (CHI) grabs and holds Favors (UTA) affecting his FOM away from the ball.
Butler (CHI) maintains legal guarding position and cleanly strips the ball from Favors (UTA).
Gasol (CHI) and Neto (UTA) make incidental contact with one another while diving for the loose ball.
Gibson (CHI) takes an additional dribble after having picked up his dribble.
Gasol (CHI) makes contact with Neto's (UTA) head that affects his shot attempt. Neto makes incidental contact with Gasol's midsection on the layup attempt during his natural jumping motion.
Gibson (CHI) sets the screen on Neto (UTA) and gives him room to avoid the contact. The two players briefly engage and separate following the screen.
Gibson (CHI) sets the screen on Hayward (UTA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Gobert (UTA) makes contact with Butler (CHI) and affects his drive to the basket.
Gasol (CHI) makes contact with Favors' (UTA) arm that affects his layup attempt.
Ingles (UTA) does not obtain a legal guarding position and makes body to body contact with Butler (CHI) that affects his RSBQ.
Gibson (CHI) makes contact with Gobert's (UTA) arm and body that affects his layup attempt.
Butler (CHI) commits a take foul on Hayward (UTA).
Johnson (UTA) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact that does not affect McDermott's (CHI) FOM away from the ball.
